mber of the executive board mr sanzone has more than  years of experience in the financial services industry and has served as chief information officer and chief administration officer at some of the world’s largest global financial institutions he served as member of executive board at credit suisse group ag from january  to february   he served as chief information officer of credit suisse ag until february  he served as chief information officer of credit suisse group ag since august   where he was charged with strategically leveraging technology globally across credit suisse including the enablement of existing and new business lines the automation of critical processes and the improvement of credit suisses overall control environment prior to that he served as chief information officer for citigroups corporate and investment bank from  to  and the global transaction services business in this role he was responsible for the strategy development and implementation of all application technology for corporate and investment banking he was the head of cib tech services mr sanzone joined salomon brothers in  as a programmer analyst in the mortgage trading systems area he served as senior operating officer for fixed income and equity sales trading since and also served as managing director and head of global application development since  at travelerssalomon smith barney he was responsible for capital markets development and was instrumental in mergerrelated systems consolidations for nikko salomon smith barney citicorp and others from  to  mr sanzone serves as a trustee of hofstra university he received a bs in computer science from hofstra university in read full background corporate headquarters  riverside avenuejacksonville florida united statesphone fax  board members memberships there is no board members memberships data available education bs hofstra university other affiliations merrill lynch  co incbooz allen hamilton holding corporationcredit suisse group a